  "articleSummary": "The article \"Promise Gotchas\" is a tutorial aimed at JavaScript developers, highlighting common pitfalls when using Promises. Its core thesis is that Promises behave differently from other values and can silently accept mistakes, leading to bugs. Key points include the necessity of using `.then()` to access resolved values (rather than direct logging) and the fact that `.then()` and `.catch()` accept `null` or `undefined` without warning, causing unintentional skipping of steps. The tone is instructive and example-driven, using a quiz to illustrate how passing `console.log()` (a function call) instead of `console.log` (a reference) results in undefined and no output.",
